From: Guoqing Jiang <Guoqing.Jiang@windriver.com>
Date: Wed, 17 Jul 2013 11:16:28 +0800
Subject: [PATCH 38/57] ARM: keystone: add KConfig option for
 KEYSTONE2_DMA_COHERENT

Commit 7ac12cb68fe851338dab7fa4da2384c83b8cd0e8 from arago tree
git://arago-project.org/git/projects/linux-keystone.git releases/03.00.00.11/master

This will allow dma coherency to be enabled for Keystone2 devices and
turn off the same for Keystone devices.

Signed-off-by: Murali Karicheri <m-karicheri2@ti.com>
Signed-off-by: Guoqing Jiang <Guoqing.Jiang@windriver.com>
---
 arch/arm/mach-keystone/Kconfig | 4 ++++
 1 file changed, 4 insertions(+)

diff --git a/arch/arm/mach-keystone/Kconfig b/arch/arm/mach-keystone/Kconfig
index 2409b93..10d56b1 100644
--- a/arch/arm/mach-keystone/Kconfig
+++ b/arch/arm/mach-keystone/Kconfig
@@ -5,6 +5,10 @@ config TI_KEYSTONE
 
 menu "TI KeyStone Implementations"
 
+config KEYSTONE2_DMA_COHERENT
+	bool "MPAX based coherency support"
+	default n
+
 endmenu
 
 endif
